org.gridgain.grid.spi.swapspace.file
Class GridFileSwapSpaceSpi

java.lang.Object
  org.gridgain.grid.spi.GridSpiAdapter
      org.gridgain.grid.spi.swapspace.file.GridFileSwapSpaceSpi
All Implemented Interfaces:
GridSpi, GridSpiJsonConfigurable, GridSpiManagementMBean, GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean, GridSwapSpaceSpi
@GridSpiInfo(author="GridGain Systems, Inc.",
             url="www.gridgain.com",
             email="support@gridgain.com",
             version="3.5.1c.18112011")
@GridSpiMultipleInstancesSupport(value=true)
public class GridFileSwapSpaceSpi
extends GridSpiAdapter
implements GridSwapSpaceSpi, GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean

File-based implementation of swap space SPI.

Key-value pairs are stored by this implementation in separate files on disk.

Separate directories are created for each space under root folder configured via GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String). Spaces (and their directory structure) are seamlessly initialized on first store to space. Name reserved for default (or null) space is represented by GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_SPACE_NAME.

Configuration

Mandatory

This SPI has no mandatory configuration parameters.

Optional

  • Root folder path (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String)).
  • Root folder index range (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderIndexRange(int)).
  • Persistent (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setPersistent(boolean)).
  • Delete corrupted files (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setDeleteCorrupted(boolean)).
  • Max swap size (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxSwapSize(long)).
  • Max swap size map (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxSwapSizeMap(Map)).
  • Max swap count (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxSwapCount(long)).
  • Max swap count map (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxSwapSizeMap(Map)).
  • Size overflow ratio (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setSizeOverflowRatio(double)).
  • Count overflow ratio (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setCountOverflowRatio(double)).
  • Workers pool size (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setPoolSize(int)).
  • Task queue capacity (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setTaskQueueCapacity(int)).
  • Max index file size (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxIndexFileSize(int)).
  • Max index buffer size (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setMaxIndexBufferSize(int)).
  • Index overflow ratio (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setIndexOverflowRatio(double)).
  • Index read batch size (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setIndexReadBatchSize(int)).
  • Eviction session timeout (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setEvictionSessionTimeout(int)).
  • Sync delay (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setSyncDelay(int)).
  • Sub-folders count (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setSubFoldersCount(int)).
  • Nested path length (see GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setNestedPathLength(int)).

Java Example

GridFileSwapSpaceSpi is used by default and should be explicitly configured only if some SPI configuration parameters need to be overridden. 
 GridFileSwapSpaceSpi spi = new GridFileSwapSpaceSpi();

 // Configure root folder path.
 spi.setRootFolderPath("/path/to/swap/folder");

 // Set pool size.
 spi.setPoolSize(20);

 GridConfigurationAdapter cfg = new GridConfigurationAdapter();

 // Override default swap space SPI.
 cfg.setSwapSpaceSpi(spi);

 // Starts grid.
 G.start(cfg);

Spring Example

GridFileSwapSpaceSpi can be configured from Spring XML configuration file: 
 <bean id="grid.cfg" class="org.gridgain.grid.GridConfigurationAdapter" scope="singleton">
     ...
     <property name="swapSpaceSpi">
         <bean class="org.gridgain.grid.spi.swapspace.file.GridFileSwapSpaceSpi">
             <property name="rootFolderPath" value="/path/to/swap/folder"/>
             <property name="poolSize" value="20"/>
         </bean>
     </property>
     ...
 </bean>


For information about Spring framework visit www.springframework.org

DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH

public static final String DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH
Default directory path for swap files location. Grid name, node ID and index (only if necessary) will be appended to this path using dashes as separators.

If GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not configured and GRIDGAIN_HOME system property is set, this folder will be created under GRIDGAIN_HOME.

If GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not configured and GRIDGAIN_HOME system property is not set, this folder will be created under java.io.tmpdir.

setRootFolderPath

@GridSpiConfiguration(optional=true)
public void setRootFolderPath(String rootFolderPath)
Sets path to a directory where swap space values will be stored. The path can either be absolute or relative to GRIDGAIN_HOME system or environment variable.

If not provided, default value is GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH.

Parameters:
rootFolderPath - Absolute or GridGain installation home folder relative path where swap space values will be stored.

getRootFolderIndexRange

public int getRootFolderIndexRange()

Specified by:
getRootFolderIndexRange in interface GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean
Returns:
Root folder index range.

setRootFolderIndexRange

@GridSpiConfiguration(optional=true)
public void setRootFolderIndexRange(int rootFolderIdxRange)
Sets root folder index range value.

If GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is not set and default path is locked (e.g. by other grid running on the same host) SPI will try next folder appending index to GRIDGAIN_HOME/GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_PATH. If GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.setRootFolderPath(String) is set, SPI tries to lock configured path only and this parameter is ignored.

If not provided, default value is GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_ROOT_FOLDER_IDX_RANGE.

Parameters:
rootFolderIdxRange - Root folder index range.

public void setMaxIndexBufferSize(int maxIdxBufSize)
Sets max index entries count in index buffer (per space).

Whenever swap entry is stored, index entry is added to space buffer. Buffer is flushed to disk once it reaches configured size.

If not provided, default value is GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_MAX_IDX_BUF_SIZE.

Parameters:
maxIdxBufSize - Max index entries count in buffer.

public double getIndexOverflowRatio()
Gets index overflow ratio.

When total index files size grows for space and becomes greater than space entries count * average index entry length * #getIndexOverflowRatio() SPI initiates index compacting by removing obsolete index entries.

getSyncDelay

public int getSyncDelay()
Gets sync delay in ms.

This property is critical for evictions.

When SPI writes entry to file it does not force underlying storage sync for better performance. Index entry for corresponding swap entry is written with System.currentTimeMillis() timestamp. There probably can be a delay before all OS buffers associated with entry file are flushed and actual file modification date may be a bit greater than one in the index. If index timestamp + syncDelay is greater tha file modification date, then index entry is considered to be valid and file can be evicted.

Specified by:
getSyncDelay in interface GridFileSwapSpaceSpiMBean
Returns:
Sync delay.

setSyncDelay

@GridSpiConfiguration(optional=true)
public void setSyncDelay(int syncDelay)
Sets sync delay in ms.

This property is critical for evictions.

When SPI writes entry to file it does not force underlying storage sync for better performance. Index entry for corresponding swap entry is written with System.currentTimeMillis() timestamp. There probably can be a delay before all OS buffers associated with entry file are flushed and actual file modification date may be a bit greater than one in the index. If index timestamp + syncDelay is greater tha file modification date, then index entry is considered to be valid and file can be evicted.

If not provided, default value is GridFileSwapSpaceSpi.DFLT_SYNC_DELAY.

Parameters:

public void spiStop()
             throws GridSpiException
This method is called to stop SPI. After this method returns kernel assumes that this SPI is finished and all resources acquired by it are released.

Note that this method can be called at any point including during recovery of failed start. It should make no assumptions on what state SPI will be in when this method is called.
